29/12/2002
ZAGREB, Croatia -- President Stipe Mesic on Friday (27 December) made several changes within the military command.
Lt Gen Marijan Marekovic was appointed commander of the Croatian Army Ground Forces, while Brig Gen Viktor Koprivnjak was relieved of duty as Air Force Chief-of-Staff and appointed Air Force Commander.
Also, Zdravko Kardum was relieved of duty as commander of the Croatian Navy Fleet and appointed Navy Commander.
The changes, proposed by the army chief-of-staff, were approved by the defence minister.
(HINA - 27/12/02)
